}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Crowley is a [[vegetarian]] and practices [[Transcendental Meditation technique|Transcendental Meditation]].<ref name="LA Times"/><ref>{{cite news|last=McCarthy|first=Ellen|title=Candy Crowley, veteran CNN reporter, takes on competitive Sunday morning slot |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/08/23/AR2010082304653.html|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=August 24, 2010}}</ref> She is divorced,<ref>{{cite news  |first=Ellen |last=McCarthy |date=August 26, 2010 |accessdate=July 24, 2013 |url=http://www.thepeninsulaqatar.com/culture/124501-cnn-host-candy-crowley-anchored-in-nuance.html|newspaper=The Peninsula|title=CNN Host Candy Crowley anchored in nuance}}</ref> and has two children and two stepchildren. Her elder child is a neurosurgeon and her younger son a musician.<ref>{{cite news |first=Ellen |last=McCarthy |date=August 30, 2010|url=http://www.heraldextra.com/lifestyles/cnn-s-new-anchor-candy-crowley-is-not-your-typical/article_41d1f55f-6d5c-5b11-99db-0b80f1fba89b.html|title=CNN’s new anchor Candy Crowley is not your typical broadcaster|publisher=''The Daily Herald''|accessdate=August 4, 2013}}</ref> Crowley is not related to [[Fox News]] correspondent [[Monica Crowley]].

